### Test Teams API with Authentication

# First, login to get a token (replace with actual credentials)
POST https://localhost:7072/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Get all teams (requires authentication)
GET https://localhost:7072/api/teams
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### Get specific team (requires authentication)
GET https://localhost:7072/api/teams/{{team_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### Create new team (requires authentication)
POST https://localhost:7072/api/teams
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Team",
  "sport": "Basketball",
  "category": "Senior",
  "gender": 2,
  "level": 1,
  "description": "Test team for authentication"
}

### Update team (requires authentication)
PUT https://localhost:7072/api/teams/{{team_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Test Team",
  "sport": "Basketball",
  "category": "Senior",
  "gender": 2,
  "level": 0,
  "description": "Updated test team"
}

### Delete team (requires authentication)
DELETE https://localhost:7072/api/teams/{{team_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}